{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SurfaceResistance",
        "description": "ModelingToolkit implementation of the surface (canopy) resistance to gaseous dry deposition from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006), Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics, 2nd ed., Chapter 19 (Dry Deposition), Eqs. 19.50-19.52 -- the Wesely (1989) resistance model. Computes the total surface resistance r_c [s/m] as four parallel deposition pathways (Eq. 19.50): the combined stomatal+mesophyll pathway, the cuticular/outer-surface pathway r_lu, the lower-canopy pathway r_dc+r_cl, and the ground pathway r_ac+r_gs. The stomatal resistance r_st (Eq. 19.51) responds to solar irradiance G and surface temperature T_s through dimensionless light and temperature factors; the mesophyll resistance r_m (Eq. 19.52) is set by the gas's effective Henry's-law solubility H_star and reactivity f_0. Migrated from AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79 src/seinfeld_pandis_ch19.jl:311 (the SurfaceResistance @component). Purely algebraic: no differential states, six explicit equations evaluated as a triangular cascade.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_deposition",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "sp-ch19",
            "dry-deposition",
            "surface-resistance",
            "wesely-1989"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDeposition.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-ug1i)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change (2nd ed.), Chapter 19: Dry Deposition, Eqs. 19.50-19.52. John Wiley & Sons, Inc."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Wesely, M. L. (1989). Parameterization of surface resistances to gaseous dry deposition in regional-scale numerical models. Atmospheric Environment 23(6), 1293-1304. doi:10.1016/0004-6981(89)90153-4"
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SurfaceResistance": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change (2nd ed.), Ch. 19, Eqs. 19.50-19.52 (Wesely 1989 surface-resistance model). John Wiley & Sons, Inc.",
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDeposition.jl@e4468c79c8dd4aae88646cd16d6bcf290874742c:src/seinfeld_pandis_ch19.jl:311\n\nUpstream `SurfaceResistance` is a flat MTK `@component` -- `System(eqs, t)` with no subsystems -- implementing Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Eqs. 19.50-19.52, the Wesely (1989) bulk surface-resistance model. It has six algebraic equations and no time derivative, so it is a purely algebraic (triangular) system; `system_kind` is left unset, the triangular-algebraic convention of the sibling wesley1989/surface_resistance.esm migration. The six equations are kept in upstream order, which is already a valid topological order (T_s_C and G_factor first, then T_factor, then r_st; r_m independently; r_c last, consuming r_st and r_m).\n\nConstants. The upstream `@constants` block (T_ref, G_ref, G_offset, T_coeff, T_max, H_coeff, f_coeff) migrates as fixed-default `parameter`s: the ESM schema has no `constant` variable type, so every `@constant` becomes a parameter carrying its numeric value as `default`. None of the seven constant names collides with the schema's reserved physical-constant names (R, k_B, N_A).\n\nInput variables. Upstream, G (solar irradiance) and T_s (surface temperature) are `@variables` with no defining equation in the standalone component -- they are inputs, wired in by the parent `DryDepositionGas` system via `surf.G ~ G` and `surf.T_s ~ T_s`. A standalone migration has no such parent, so G and T_s are migrated as `parameter`s, matching the wesley1989/surface_resistance.esm treatment of its scalar input arguments. The six genuinely-computed `@variables` (T_s_C, G_factor, T_factor, r_st, r_m, r_c) migrate as `type: state` with explicit algebraic equations, preserving 1:1 symmetry with the upstream `@variables` block.\n\nParameter defaults. Upstream declares no defaults for its `@parameters`. The migrated defaults describe SO2 dry deposition over a midsummer deciduous forest: the gas-property triple (D_ratio=1.9, H_star=1e5, f_0=0) is the S&P Table 19.4 SO2 row, and the land-use resistances (r_i=70, r_lu=2000, r_ac=2000, r_cl=2000, r_gs=500 s/m) are the deciduous-forest / midsummer / SO2 entries of the Wesely 1989 tables -- the same season x land-use cell asserted by wesley1989/surface_resistance.esm's `default_midsummer_so2` test. r_dc=100 s/m is a representative lower-canopy buoyant-convection resistance (tabulated here as a direct parameter). G=300 W/m^2 and T_s=298.15 K (25 degC) are mid-range daytime conditions.\n\nUnits. H_star is dimensionless in this formulation (the effective Henry's-law constant normalized; upstream `unit = u\"1\"`), so the mesophyll coefficients H_coeff [m/s] and f_coeff [m/s] make r_m = 1/(H_coeff*H_star + f_coeff*f_0) come out in s/m. ESM `units` fields are descriptive only; the runners perform no dimensional analysis.\n\nSingularities. The temperature factor T_factor = T_coeff/(T_s_C*(T_max - T_s_C)) is singular at T_s_C = 0 and T_s_C = 40 (T_s = 273.15 K and 313.15 K); the light factor G_factor is singular at G = -G_offset = -0.1 W/m^2, and the small G_offset keeps G = 0 well-defined. Every test and example evaluation stays strictly interior (T_s_C in [5, 35] degC, G >= 0).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): a closed-form explicit algebraic system with no ODE integration. The expected values are the Float64 evaluation of Eqs. 19.50-19.52; rel=1e-6 absorbs round-off across the reciprocal-sum chain, well above the bit-level agreement expected between conforming runners."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-06
            },
            "variables": {
                "T_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 273.15,
                    "description": "Celsius-to-Kelvin offset applied to the surface temperature (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "G_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 200.0,
                    "description": "Reference solar irradiance in the stomatal light response, Eq. 19.51 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "G_offset": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.1,
                    "description": "Small irradiance offset that keeps the light factor finite at G = 0 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "T_coeff": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K^2",
                    "default": 400.0,
                    "description": "Temperature coefficient of the stomatal temperature factor, Eq. 19.51 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "T_max": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 40.0,
                    "description": "Upper temperature bound (Celsius-equivalent) of stomatal function in Eq. 19.51 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "H_coeff": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.00033,
                    "description": "Henry's-law coefficient of the mesophyll resistance, Eq. 19.52 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "f_coeff": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Reactivity coefficient of the mesophyll resistance, Eq. 19.52 (upstream @constant)."
                },
                "H_star": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 100000.0,
                    "description": "Effective Henry's-law constant of the depositing gas (dimensionless, normalized; S&P Table 19.4). Default: SO2."
                },
                "f_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Chemical reactivity factor of the depositing gas, 0-1 (S&P Table 19.4). Default: SO2."
                },
                "D_ratio": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.9,
                    "description": "Ratio of water-vapor to gas molecular diffusivity, D_H2O/D_gas (S&P Table 19.4). Default: SO2."
                },
                "r_i": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 70.0,
                    "description": "Minimum bulk-canopy stomatal resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: deciduous forest, midsummer."
                },
                "r_lu": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 2000.0,
                    "description": "Cuticular / outer-canopy-surface resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: deciduous forest, midsummer."
                },
                "r_dc": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 100.0,
                    "description": "Lower-canopy buoyant-convection resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: representative midsummer value."
                },
                "r_cl": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 2000.0,
                    "description": "Lower-canopy exposed-surfaces uptake resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: deciduous forest, midsummer, SO2."
                },
                "r_ac": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 2000.0,
                    "description": "In-canopy aerodynamic resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: deciduous forest, midsummer."
                },
                "r_gs": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "default": 500.0,
                    "description": "Ground-surface uptake resistance (Wesely 1989 land-use table). Default: deciduous forest, midsummer, SO2."
                },
                "G": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Solar irradiance reaching the surface. Upstream a connected @variable; an input parameter in the standalone migration."
                },
                "T_s": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.15,
                    "description": "Surface temperature. Upstream a connected @variable; an input parameter in the standalone migration."
                },
                "T_s_C": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "K",
                    "description": "Surface temperature offset from the 273.15 K reference (Celsius-equivalent magnitude carried with a K unit)."
                },
                "G_factor": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless irradiance factor of the stomatal resistance, 1 + (G_ref/(G+G_offset))^2 (Eq. 19.51)."
                },
                "T_factor": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless temperature factor of the stomatal resistance, T_coeff/(T_s_C*(T_max-T_s_C)) (Eq. 19.51)."
                },
                "r_st": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "description": "Bulk-canopy stomatal resistance (Eq. 19.51)."
                },
                "r_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "description": "Mesophyll resistance (Eq. 19.52)."
                },
                "r_c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "s/m",
                    "description": "Total surface (canopy) resistance to gaseous dry deposition along four parallel pathways (Eq. 19.50)."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "_comment": "Temperature offset from the 273.15 K reference: T_s_C = T_s - T_ref.",
                    "lhs": "T_s_C",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            "T_s",
                            "T_ref"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.51 light factor: G_factor = 1 + (G_ref/(G + G_offset))^2.",
                    "lhs": "G_factor",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            "G_ref",
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "G",
                                                    "G_offset"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    2
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.51 temperature factor: T_factor = T_coeff/(T_s_C*(T_max - T_s_C)).",
                    "lhs": "T_factor",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            "T_coeff",
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "T_s_C",
                                    {
                                        "op": "-",
                                        "args": [
                                            "T_max",
                                            "T_s_C"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.51 stomatal resistance: r_st = D_ratio*r_i*G_factor*T_factor.",
                    "lhs": "r_st",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "D_ratio",
                            "r_i",
                            "G_factor",
                            "T_factor"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.52 mesophyll resistance: r_m = 1/(H_coeff*H_star + f_coeff*f_0).",
                    "lhs": "r_m",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "H_coeff",
                                            "H_star"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "f_coeff",
                                            "f_0"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 19.50 total surface resistance: four parallel deposition pathways.",
                    "lhs": "r_c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "r_st",
                                                    "r_m"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            "r_lu"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "r_dc",
                                                    "r_cl"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            1,
                                            {
                                                "op": "+",
                                                "args": [
                                                    "r_ac",
                                                    "r_gs"
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_so2_deciduous",
                    "description": "Default case: SO2 over a midsummer deciduous forest, G = 300 W/m^2, T_s = 298.15 K (25 degC). All four S&P Eq. 19.50 pathways carry their default land-use resistances. r_c is re-checked at t = 1 s to confirm this algebraic system is time-invariant.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "D_ratio": 1.9,
                        "H_star": 100000.0,
                        "f_0": 0.0,
                        "r_i": 70.0,
                        "r_lu": 2000.0,
                        "r_dc": 100.0,
                        "r_cl": 2000.0,
                        "r_ac": 2000.0,
                        "r_gs": 500.0,
                        "G": 300.0,
                        "T_s": 298.15
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "T_s_C",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 25.0
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "G_factor",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.44414829623048
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "T_factor",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.0666666666666667
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "r_st",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 204.87650495856408
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "r_m",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.030303030303030304
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "r_c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 159.83485089186416
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "r_c",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 159.83485089186416
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
